8 An Act relating to commercial driver licenses;
creating the Ray Davis Safe Roads Act; amending 47
9 O.S. 2021, Section 6-101, as last amended by Section
3, Chapter 330, O.S.L. 2025 (47 O.S. Supp. 2025,
10 Section 6-101), which relates to class requirements
for driver licenses; prohibiting the issuance of
11 commercial driver license to certain individuals;
amending 47 O.S. 2021, Section 6-103, as amended by
12 Section 40, Chapter 282, O.S.L. 2022 (47 O.S. Supp.
2025, Section 6-103), which relates to persons not to
13 be licensed; prohibiting the issuance of commercial
driver license to certain individuals; requiring
14 Service Oklahoma make certain verification; modifying
list of persons not to be licensed; providing for
15 noncodification; and providing an effective date.
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
19 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
20 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Ray Davis Safe
21 Roads Act".
22 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 6-101, as
23 last amended by Section 3, Chapter 330, O.S.L. 2025 (47 O.S. Supp.
24 2025, Section 6-101), is amended to read as follows:
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB3304 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 Section 6-101. A. No person, except those hereinafter
2 expressly exempted in Sections 6-102 and 6-102.1 of this title,
3 shall operate any motor vehicle upon a highway in this state unless
4 the person has a valid Oklahoma driver license for the class of
5 vehicle being operated under the provisions of this title. No
6 person shall be permitted to possess more than one valid license at
7 any time, except as provided in paragraph 4 5 of subsection F of
8 this section.
9 B. 1. No person shall operate a Class A commercial motor
10 vehicle unless the person is eighteen (18) years of age or older and
11 holds a valid Class A commercial license, except as provided in
12 paragraph 5 of this subsection and subsection F of this section.
13 Any person holding a valid Class A commercial license shall be
14 permitted to operate motor vehicles in Classes A, B, C and D, except
15 as provided for in paragraph 4 of this subsection.
16 2. No person shall operate a Class B commercial motor vehicle
17 unless the person is eighteen (18) years of age or older and holds a
18 valid Class B commercial license, except as provided in paragraph 5
19 6 of subsection F of this section. Any person holding a valid Class
20 B commercial license shall be permitted to operate motor vehicles in
21 Classes B, C and D, except as provided for in paragraph 4 of this
22 subsection.
23 3. No person shall operate a Class C commercial motor vehicle
24 unless the person is eighteen (18) years of age or older and holds a
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB3304 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 vali d Class C commercial license, except as provided in subsection F
2 of this section. Any person holding a valid Class C commercial
3 license shall be permitted to operate motor vehicles in Classes C
4 and D, except as provided for in paragraph 4 of this subsection.
5 4. No person under twenty-one (21) years of age shall be
6 licensed to operate any motor vehicle which is required to be
7 placarded for hazardous materials pursuant to 49 C.F.R., Part 172,
8 subpart F, except as provided in subsection F of this section;
9 provided, a person eighteen (18) years of age or older may be
10 licensed to operate a farm vehicle which is required to be placarded
11 for hazardous materials pursuant to 49 C.F.R., Part 172, subpart F,
12 except as provided in subsection F of this section.
13 5. A person at least seventeen (17) years of age who
14 successfully completes all examinations required by law may be
15 issued by Service Oklahoma:
16 a. a restricted Class A commercial license which shall
17 grant to the licensee the privilege to operate a Class
18 A or Class B commercial motor vehicle for harvest
19 purposes or a Class D motor vehicle, or
20 b. a restricted Class B commercial license which shall
21 grant to the licensee the privilege to operate a Class
22 B commercial motor vehicle for harvest purposes or a
23 Class D motor vehicle.
24
