14 F. 1. Any person eighteen (18) years of age or older may apply
15 for a restricted Class A, B or C commercial learner permit. Service
16 Oklahoma, after the applicant has passed all parts of the
17 examination for a Class D license and has successfully passed all
18 parts of the examination for a Class A, B or C commercial license
19 other than the driving examination, may issue to the applicant a
20 commercial learner permit which shall entitle the person having
21 immediate lawful possession of the commercial learner permit and a
22 valid Oklahoma driver license or provisional driver license pursuant
23 to Section 6-212 of this title to operate a Class A, B or C
24 commercial motor vehicle upon the public highways solely for the
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB3304 SFLR Page 5
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 purp ose of behind-the-wheel training in accordance with rules
2 promulgated by the Department.
3 2. This commercial learner permit shall be issued for a period
4 as provided in Section 6-115 of this title of one (1) year;
5 provided, such commercial learner permit may be suspended, revoked,
6 canceled, denied or disqualified at the discretion of the
7 Department, with notice to Service Oklahoma, for violation of the
8 restrictions, for failing to give the required or correct
9 information on the application or for violation of any traffic laws
10 of this state pertaining to the operation of a motor vehicle.
11 Except as otherwise provided, the lawful possessor of a commercial
12 learner permit who has been issued a commercial learner permit for a
13 minimum of fourteen (14) days may have the restriction requiring an
14 accompanying driver removed by satisfactorily completing a driver's
15 examination; provided, the removal of a restriction shall not
16 authorize the operation of a Class A, B or C commercial motor
17 vehicle if such operation is otherwise prohibited by law.
18 3. Service Oklahoma shall not issue an original Class A, B, or
19 C driver license to any applicant who is disqualified under
20 paragraph 5 of subsection A of Section 6-103 of this title.
21 4. No person shall apply for and Service Oklahoma shall not
22 issue an original Class A, B or C driver license until the person
23 has been issued a commercial learner permit and held the permit for
24 at least fourteen (14) days. Any person who currently holds a Class
