4 Section 6-103. A. Except as otherwise provided by law, Service
5 Oklahoma shall not issue a driver license to:
6 1. Any person who is under eighteen (18) years of age, except
7 that Service Oklahoma may issue a Class D license to any person who
8 attains sixteen (16) years of age on or after August 15, 2000, and
9 meets the requirements of Sections 6-105 and 6-107.3 of this title;
10 2. Any unemancipated person who is under eighteen (18) years of
11 age and whose custodial legal parent or legal guardian does not
12 approve the issuance of a license as required by Section 6-110.2 of
13 this title or objects to the issuance of a license or permit by
14 filing an objection pursuant to Section 6-103.1 of this title;
15 3. Any person whose driving privilege has been suspended,
16 revoked, canceled or denied in this state or any other state or
17 country until the driving privilege has been reinstated by the state
18 or country withdrawing the privilege;
19 4. Any person who is classified as an excessive user of
20 alcohol, any other intoxicating substance, or a combination of
21 alcohol and any other intoxicating substance, and inimical to public
22 safety, in accordance with rules promulgated by the Department,
23 until all requirements granting or reinstating driving privileges
24 are met, including, but not limited to, abstinence from the use of
