1 alco hol, any other intoxicating substance, or any combination of
2 alcohol and any other intoxicating substance for a minimum of either
3 twelve (12) months or eighteen (18) months, as determined by OAC
4 595:10-5, immediately preceding application for or application for
5 reinstatement of driving privileges;
6 5. Any applicant for a Class A, B, or C commercial driver
7 license whose name appears on the methamphetamine offender registry
8 maintained pursuant to Section 2-701 of Title 63 of the Oklahoma
9 Statutes. Prior to the issuance of a commercial driver license,
10 Service Oklahoma shall verify, via a data match or other appropriate
11 means, that the applicant is not on the registry;
12 6. Any person who is required by Section 6-101 et seq. of this
13 title to take an examination, unless the person shall have
14 successfully passed the examination;
15 6. 7. Any person who is required under the laws of this state
16 to deposit proof of financial responsibility and who has not
17 deposited such proof;
18 7. 8. Any person who is physically deformed or who is afflicted
